reviewText:
Most idiots who fell for a masterful marketing ploy are clueless. BLADE RUNNER, original/International Cut is my preference. So many who diss the narration and 'happy ending' are just tools. BLADE RUNNER was made pretty much the way Ridley Scott wanted it. If you hadn't seen the newer versions, no one would have known the difference;
Warner Bros played you as fools...and made a killing. Just the way they planned it.
Also most who diss the narration, have had the benefit of viewing it, first, and KNOW the story line. So like sheep , they can now dispense with that version; Again, probably 90% of the situation is a marketing ploy, and many fell for it hook, line and sinker; Show the DC to a stranger to the film and they will lose out on a deeper understanding of what is going on. Like George Lucas, who tried to modernize Star Wars and worse THX 1138, who claims the newest is the best. The new versions of BR are simply a way to get you to buy the Blu Ray all over again. Ive read everything there is to read on the subject, and I read articles, back in 1982, where Scott was asked if the "narration" was forced on him. He denied it quite fervently. He is revising his statements, going along with the marketing campaign. I also am wondering if the Blu Ray is really significantly better than the 2007 DVD. With an OPPO 103 player, I'm wonder about the urge to buy even a few things all over again. A-B ing the combo DVD/BR editions of OBLIVION, PICNIC AT HANGING ROCK, etc-I can see little or no difference-comparing them. The 1080 upscaling of the DVD...makes it seem redundant to buy my DVDs all over again. Maybe if you have a HUGE screen it may make a difference-I have a 40";
Again people are too easily led into the NEW! BETTER! MORE! dumb consumer philosophy. The only disc i will buy over again are discs are favorites transferred before 2005, or SEs that are restored in 4k. I have the new (2015) 1959 restored, 4k version of JOURNEY TO THE CENTER OF THE EARTH, and it is stunning.
End of discussion
